overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review and enhancement task for
  their interactive sleep questionnaire application. The assistant meticulously
  analyzed the existing codebase against the detailed project specification and
  Statement of Work, identifying several critical gaps. The approach involved a
  phased implementation of missing features. Key decisions included integrating
  a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with immediate safety warnings for high
  scores, developing explicit detection and reporting for COMISA (Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and adding a
  dedicated section for external educational and clinical resources in both the
  web and PDF versions of the patient report. The outcome is a significantly
  more robust and informative questionnaire, providing enhanced diagnostic
  insights and actionable guidance to users. The assistant is continuing to
  address the remaining identified improvements.
